Cell.Text: Taking this man to be interrogated.
Where are you taking your prisoner?
That is none of your concern.
[S] He has knowledge of a cult of Talos. He will tell us what we need to know, or he will die. The choice is his.
<<Shared>> Now, get of my way.
[S] G|<<Shared>> Now, get of my way.
[S] By Imperial Law banning Talos, we have the right to do whatever we want.

Node.Caption: WEThalmorDialogueWhatRight: What right do you have to drag people away like this?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> And now you'll walk away, if you know what's good for you.
[S] G|<<Shared>> And now you'll walk away, if you know what's good for you.
[S] Or perhaps there's something you'd like to confess?
[S] G|<<Shared>> And so, you will die a heretic's death.

Node.Caption: WEThalmorDialogueBelieveInTalose: You got me. I believe in Talos.

Cell.Text: Incorrect. You can worship whatever gods you like. But Talos is a man. Only a heretic would think otherwise...

Node.Caption: WEThalmorDialogueBelieveWhatever: I can worship anyone I want.

Cell.Text: I don't like you... I think you're a heretic.
I am a Thalmor Justiciar on important business that you are interfering with.
Do all Thalmor have such high opinions of themselves?
[S] That we are superior to men is an established fact. For example, take this belief in Talos. The "ninth" divine. Heh. | Certainly you don't believe such things?
We are special envoys of the Aldmeri Dominion, the rightful rulers of Tamriel. If you'd like I can show you why.
<<Shared>> If you're smart, you'll walk away.
[S] G|<<Shared>> If you're smart, you'll walk away.
We're making sure your Emperor wasn't lying to his elven masters when he agreed the Empire would give up false gods and foolish beliefs.

Node.Caption: WEThalmorDialogueDoingInSkyrim: What are you doing in Skyrim?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Now, go away.
[S] G|<<Shared>> Now, go away.
It's immoral to worship a man. And it's also illegal. A faithful Imperial citizen would know that.
[S] <<Shared>> Perhaps there's something you wish to confess?
